verbose_text: These data not only suggest that the increase in VOR gain allowed the Shisa6 L7 KO mice to compensate for their impairments in optokinetic control under normal conditions in which the light is present, but they also highlight that the learning deficits that occurred during the visuo-vestibular mismatch training described above cannot be linked to an inability to detect and track the visual stimulus when combined with a vestibular input.
